The '''Order of the Mother of Jugović''' ({{lang-sr|Орден мајке Југовића}}) is an [[order (honour)|order]] awarded by the [[Serbian Orthodox Church]] to [[mother]]s who have multiple [[child]]ren. It is named after the "Mother of the [[Jugović brothers]]"<ref>{{cite book|author=Jovan Ilić|title=The Serbian question in the Balkans|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=J1UtAQAAIAAJ|year=1995|publisher=Faculty of Geography, University of Belgrade}}</ref> who, in [[Serbian epic poetry]], had nine sons and a daughter.

The silver order is awarded to mothers who gave birth to four children, while the golden order is awarded to mothers with five or more children.<ref>Eparhija raško-prizrenska i kosovsko-metohijska: [http://www.novinar.de/2009/07/08/vidovdan.html Vidovdan]</ref>

